SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 2223
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE RIGGS.
4138H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 226, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the statewide
transportation improvement program.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 226, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 226.034, to read as follows:
226.034. 1. Any member of the general assembly, county commissioner, or
2 mayor of a city, town, or village who is dissatisfied with any action or decision included
3 in the statewide transportation improvement program (STIP) may seek review of such
4 action or decision by the administrative hearing commission. Such review shall be
5 sought by the filing of a petition with the administrative hearing commission within
6 thirty days of the publication date of the annual STIP. If any such petition is sent by
7 registered mail or certified mail, it shall be deemed filed on the date it is mailed; if it is
8 sent by any method other than registered mail or certified mail, it shall be deemed filed
9 on the date it is received by the commission.
10 2. The procedures applicable to such hearings and determinations shall be those
11 established by chapter 536.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

